cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.IT 

This paper discusses threats to the stability and security of information-centric network infrastructure, which is a subfield of computer networking. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also analyzes the security of the content distribution system, which falls under the subfield of computer security, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the performance of routers, which is related to distributed computing, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the state-based forwarding, which is related to systems and control, cs.SI (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the content routing, which is related to information theory, cs.IT (Information Theory).
